@{    
    var appName = (string?)ViewBag.AppName ?? "Trucks Weighing Web App";
    ViewData["Title"] = "Privacy Policy — " + appName;
    ViewData["Description"] = $"How {appName} handles and protects your data.";
    var canonicalUrl = $"{Context.Request.Scheme}://{Context.Request.Host}/privacy";
}
@* <h1>@ViewData["Title"]</h1>
<p>Use this page to detail your site's privacy policy.</p> *@

@section Head {
    <meta name="description" content="@ViewData["Description"]" />
    <link rel="canonical" href="@canonicalUrl" />

    <!-- JSON-LD -->
    <script type="application/ld+json">
        {
          "@@context":"https://schema.org",
          "@@type":"PrivacyPolicy",
          "name":"Privacy Policy",
          "url":"@canonicalUrl",
          "publisher":{ "@@type":"Organization", "name":"@appName" }
        }
    </script>
}

<h1 class="mb-3">Privacy Policy</h1>
<hr />

<p class="text-muted">Last updated: October 2025</p>

<p>
    This Privacy Policy explains how we handle personal information when you use <strong>@appName</strong>.
</p>

<h2 class="h5 mt-4">1. Information We Collect</h2>
<ul>
    <li><strong>Account Information:</strong> name, email address, and password provided during registration.</li>
    <li><strong>Operational Data:</strong> data you enter into the app (e.g., inspections, truck records, survey data).</li>
    <li><strong>Technical Data:</strong> basic logs (IP, browser, timestamps) for security and performance.</li>
</ul>

<h2 class="h5 mt-4">2. How We Use the Information</h2>
<ul>
    <li>To provide secure access and core functionality of the application.</li>
    <li>To manage inspections, truck weighing records, and survey operations.</li>
    <li>To improve reliability, performance, and user experience.</li>
    <li>To contact you about your account or important updates.</li>
</ul>

<h2 class="h5 mt-4">3. Data Sharing</h2>
<p>
    We do <strong>not</strong> sell or share your personal data with third parties.
    We may disclose data only if required by law or to protect the security of the system.
</p>

<h2 class="h5 mt-4">4. Cookies and Sessions</h2>
<p>
    The application uses cookies to keep you signed in and to improve usability.
    We do not use marketing or tracking cookies.
</p>

<h2 class="h5 mt-4">5. Data Security</h2>
<ul>
    <li>Passwords are stored using secure hashing.</li>
    <li>Access to data is restricted by authentication and user roles.</li>
    <li>We apply reasonable technical and organizational measures to protect data.</li>
</ul>

<h2 class="h5 mt-4">6. Data Retention</h2>
<p>
    We retain account and operational data for as long as your account is active or as needed to provide the service. You may request deletion at any time (see “Your Rights”).
</p>

<h2 class="h5 mt-4">7. Service Providers & Hosting</h2>
<p>
    We may use reputable cloud providers (e.g., hosting, email delivery) acting as data processors on our behalf. They are bound by contractual obligations to protect your data.
</p>

<h2 class="h5 mt-4">8. Your Rights</h2>
<ul>
    <li>Request deletion of your account and associated data.</li>
    <li>Update your profile information at any time.</li>
    <li>Request a data export or ask privacy questions by contacting us.</li>
</ul>

<h2 class="h5 mt-4">9. Changes to This Policy</h2>
<p>
    We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. Material changes will be announced in the app. The “Last updated” date reflects the latest revision.
</p>

<h2 class="h5 mt-4">10. Contact</h2>
<p>
    Questions about this Privacy Policy? Please contact the application administrator.
</p>

<hr class="my-4" />
<p class="small text-muted">
    Note: This Privacy Policy is part of the application documentation and may be adapted if the app
    is deployed in different environments or maintained by other administrators.
</p>
